      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>I manage my time by organizing my tasks effectively.</p>
<p>Because I know that my time is limited, I invest some of it in organization so I can be as productive as possible with the rest of it.</p>
<p>I let go of the idea that I can do everything and focus my attention on a few things that matter most to me. I prune out the rest in order to be able to do quality work on those things without stretching myself too far.</p>
<div class="zemanta-img zemanta-action-dragged" style="margin: 1em; display: block;">
<div class="wp-caption alignright" style="width: 190px"><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Image:Variables_of_production_performance.png"><img title="Variables of production performance (Saari 2006)" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/e/e4/Variables_of_production_performance.png/300px-Variables_of_production_performance.png" alt="Variables of production performance (Saari 2006)" width="180" height="151" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text">Image via Wikipedia</p></div>
</div>
<p>Because I am clear on where I am going, I find it natural to break down the steps I need to take to get there. I set realistic daily, weekly and yearly goals so I can accomplish what I set out to do in a reasonable manner.</p>
<p>I let go of the idea that I should be able to finish important projects overnight and, instead, give myself the time I need to do an exceptional job.</p>
<p>I often have many things that I need to remember: names, dates, times, tasks, opportunities, and much more. I utilize a planner and check it regularly because I know that by staying organized I am granting myself greater productivity and a more relaxed life.</p>
<p>Self-Reflection Questions:</p>
<p>1. Do I recognize the value of investing time in organization?<br />
2. Do I take advantage of tools that are designed to help me be organized?<br />
3. Are the activities that use up my time contributing to the achievement of my goals?</p>
