</div>
<p>How to Schedule In Me-Time</p>
<p>Being a mom and an entrepreneur means there&#8217;s very little, if any, time for you to simply spend time on yourself ñ there&#8217;s very little me time.  However it&#8217;s the me time that keeps us smiling when our two year old uses a sharpie marker on the white walls or the sixteen year old crashes the car into the garage.  It&#8217;s the me time that keeps us sane and able to manage life&#8217;s little challenges.  Here are a few tips to make sure you schedule time for yourself:</p>
<p>#1  Add it to your schedule.  That sounds like a given, right?  Yet many people skip this step.  They schedule dentist appointments but not time for themselves. Seems quite backwards really, why on earth would you prefer having holes drilled in your head over a day at the spa, a good book in a park or lunch with your friends?  One great way to make sure you schedule me-time into your life is to make it a commitment.  For example, go out to lunch with friends, make a spa or massage appointment or hire a babysitter to watch the children.  This way, you&#8217;re committing to someone else as well, the massage therapist, your friends, etc and you&#8217;ll be less likely to back out.</p>
<p>#2  Make it routine.  When something becomes a habit, part of our normal routine and lifestyle, we&#8217;re more likely to do it and more likely to miss it if you skip it.  Creating regular me time whether it is daily or weekly is a great way to make and keep a commitment to take care of yourself.</p>
<p>#3  Partner up.  If you know other moms who are also entrepreneurs then they too are probably looking for a little me time.  Consider partnering with them for childcare. For example if there is a painting class you&#8217;d like to take on Wednesday mornings and she has a weekly massage on Friday afternoons, you can swap and watch each other&#8217;s children.</p>
<p>#4  Ask your family for help.  Partners and children don&#8217;t know you need me time unless you tell them.  However it pays to create a plan in advance.  Simply bursting at a stressful moment and screaming that you don&#8217;t get enough time to yourself is only going to hurt feelings. Instead, create a plan of action and present it to your family asking for their support.</p>
<p>#5  Learn to say no to others and yes to yourself. There&#8217;s always something else that needs to be done.  Always.  Learn to say no and to prioritize your tasks, keeping in mind that you are always top priority.</p>
<p>Children learn from our example. This makes self care important for your mental and physical health and it teaches your child how to take good care of themselves today and when they&#8217;re an adult.</p>
